{"lemma":"فارَّة","slug":"فارَّة","root":"ف.ر.ر","root_slug":"ف-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فارَّة","root":"فره","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32826","n33754"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to overflow, to gush forth, to boil up"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32826","headword_ar":"فَاْرَةٌ","root":"fA^r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"n. un. (but said by some to be fem.) of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^orN","text_ar":"فَاْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] ―         -b2-  Also, (S, M, O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuw^orapN","text_ar":"فُوْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K, in the O written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuw^arap","text_ar":"فُوَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",) both with and without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A flatus"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that collects"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the pastern"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which issues"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is felt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it is stroked, and collects when it is left to itself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n33754","headword_ar":"فَارِهٌ","root":"frh","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Skilful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing skill;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faruha","text_ar":"فَرُهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", irregularly formed, for by rule it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariyhN","text_ar":"فَرِيهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) accord. to Z, it is applied to a man; and also, without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayonap","text_ar":"قَيْنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. female slave, or slave-songstress]. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  And it is applied as an epithet to a hackney, (Az, S, Msb,) and a mule, (S,) and an ass, (Az, S, Msb,) or to a horse, or similar beast, (Az,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Brisk, lively, sprightly, active, agile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, * Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp; strong; that goes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeys, much; a great goer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) it is not applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faras","text_ar":"فَرَس"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, S,) i. e. to an Arabian horse; (Az, Msb;) such being termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawaAdN","text_ar":"جَوَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, S, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAy^iEN","text_ar":"رَايِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) 'Adee Ibn-Zeyd has applied it to the latter; but As has charged him with error in so doing; saying that he possessed not knowledge of horses: (S:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furohN","text_ar":"فُرْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buzolN","text_ar":"بُزْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuwlN","text_ar":"حُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAzilN","text_ar":"بَازِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAy^ilN","text_ar":"حَايِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuhN","text_ar":"فُرُهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kutubN","text_ar":"كُتُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farahapN","text_ar":"فَرَهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with two fet-hahs, (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furohapN","text_ar":"فُرْهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) but this is held by Sb to be a quasi-pl. n., (ISd, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fur~ahN","text_ar":"فُرَّهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruk~aEN","text_ar":"رُكَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fur~ahapN","text_ar":"فُرَّهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suk~arapN","text_ar":"سُكَّرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) as in the A, but MF says that no pl. of this measure is known. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gulaAm","text_ar":"غُلَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. youth, young man, or male slave],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beautiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comely, of countenance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.) And [the fem.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArihapN","text_ar":"فَارِهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"girl, or young woman: (K:) [and] so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farohaA='u","text_ar":"فَرْهَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [of which the masc. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforahu","text_ar":"اَفْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and] of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furohN","text_ar":"فُرْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but Az says, I do not think that they use this word in relation to girls, or young women, though they may apply it peculiarly to female slaves like as they apply"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArihN","text_ar":"فَارِهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArihapN","text_ar":"فَارِهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"peculiarly to hackneys and mules and jades, exclusively of Arabian horses. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArihapN","text_ar":"فَارِهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatiy~apN","text_ar":"فَتِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"youthful"},{"kind":"text","text":"females, or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the prime of life"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (thus accord. to several copies of the K and accord. to the TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qayonapN","text_ar":"قَيْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a female slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a slave-songstress:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see the first sentence of this paragraph]. (Thus in the CK.) ―         -b5-  And it signifies also [A woman]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who eats vehemently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faArihN","text_ar":"فَارِهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vehement eater."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Az","Msb","TA","K","ISd"]}]}}